 Armed gunmen suspected to be kidnappers on Monday night killed a  driver and abducted 13 passengers along Abuja-Lokoja Road. The incident occurred at Sabon-Gari Village when the hoodlums laid an ambush along the road and opened fire on moving vehicles. The gunmen, according to an eyewitness, were said to have dressed in army uniforms and shot the driver of a Toyota Highlander coming from Lokoja axis. The driver on sighting the gunmen had attempted to escape but one of the hoodlums opened fire and killed him instantly. It was gathered that an 18-seater commercial bus coming from Abaji ran into the Hoodlums, who fired gunshots  and whisked all the occupants into the bush.